MYTHIC (25+ AP) - Living Myth: FLOORS, NOT STATS
Mythic-tier enemies are not built from a table. Every number below is a MINIMUM; there are no maximums. The GM is trusted to scale upward to match what the party can actually handle - these are floors, never targets.
Stat Array floor: 22 / 20 / 18 / 16 (stats above 20 are legal at this tier)
TL 1 Minion: HP 300+ - Dmg 35+ - DR 25+
TL 2 Elite: HP 750+ - Dmg 85+ - DR 35+
TL 3 BOSS: HP 2000+ - Dmg 190+ - DR 50+
Design anchor: the Mythic Boss DR floor (50) equals the maximum SUSTAINED Damage Reduction a fully optimized player can achieve (top armor + all-crit smithing + Dragonhide + Ebonyflesh + double enchantments). A maxed player is almost a Mythic boss - the floor of this tier is the ceiling of the players.

STAT ARRAY KEY
P (Primary): The creature's main offensive/defensive stat (e.g., Might for a Warrior). They almost never fail this roll.
S (Secondary): Their backup skill (e.g., Agility for a Warrior).
T (Tertiary): A minor skill.
D (Dump): Their weakness (e.g., Magic for a Warrior). Players should target this stat with spells or maneuvers.
DAMAGE & DR RULES
Base Damage: This is the flat damage dealt by a standard attack.
Power Attacks: Add +2 Damage.
Critical Hits: Multiply Total Damage by x2.
THE STACKING LAW (Formula of Pain — see legendary difficulty's worked examples, which are the authority): add ALL flat bonuses first to build the Base Hit, then multiply ALL multipliers together. Multipliers multiply — they never add. (Example: Base 11, Sneak x3, Crit x2 = 11 x 3 x 2 = 66.) Flat x2-damage ITEMS are unique GM-granted artifacts only (e.g., Kyboh's Titan Gloves) — never a commissionable enchantment.


Damage Reduction (DR): This is subtracted from every incoming hit.
Boss DR: Bosses rely on high DR to ignore "chip damage" from weak attacks. Players must use Power Attacks, Sunder Armor, or Magic to penetrate these defenses.


BOSS MECHANICS (TL 3)
To ensure Bosses feel epic and survive high-damage player parties, apply these traits:
Villain Actions: Bosses take 1 Major Action on their turn, plus 1 Villain Action at the end of every second player's turn (e.g., Tail Swipe, Bellow, Teleport).
Phase Bars: Divide the Boss's Total HP into 2 or 3 "Bars." Damage does not carry over between bars. When a bar breaks, the Boss sheds status effects and changes tactics.



